	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85776><span id=Sage>Master Cannis</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>691 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I found this out when I went to City of Mist with some guildmates and friends. I being a ranger had never really used harmony much, but the monk I was with had a hard time splitting the mobs so I went in and harmonied and lo and behold, I could see which mobs would agro as harmony only effected the mob within agro range mob I cast it on. I cast snare on the one that it didn't effect to check pathing and after that the monk was able to pull without any problems.&nbsp;&nbsp;So next time your in a new outdoor zone and have a hard time splitting pulls get a druid or ranger to cast harmony and see which mobs are tied together in agro.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jan  9 16:37:26 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Cannis 65th Ranger<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69645" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69645</a> <br><br></td></tr>
